# CODEOWNERS - Automatic PR Review Assignment
# Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owners for everything in the repository
# Replace with specific maintainer usernames or teams as needed
* @ihelloeveryone

# Templates - require review for template changes
/templates/ @ihelloeveryone

# Documentation pillars - can assign specific pillar maintainers later
/docs/foundations/ @ihelloeveryone
/docs/hardware/ @ihelloeveryone
/docs/software/ @ihelloeveryone
/docs/systems/ @ihelloeveryone

# Repository configuration files
/.github/ @ihelloeveryone
CONTRIBUTING.md @ihelloeveryone
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md @ihelloeveryone
LICENSE @ihelloeveryone
README.md @ihelloeveryone

# To add organization teams (requires team creation first):
# Syntax: @Moebius-Order/team-name
# Example:
# /docs/foundations/algorithms/ @Moebius-Order/algorithms-team @specific-user
# /docs/hardware/digital-logic/ @Moebius-Order/hardware-team

# To add additional maintainers:
# Simply add their GitHub username with @ prefix
# Example:
# /docs/foundations/ @ihelloeveryone @another-maintainer
# /docs/systems/networking/ @networking-expert